00:23:00,000 --> 00:23:01,640
She's been around you the whole time.

584
00:23:01,840 --> 00:23:02,920
Why are you asking me?

585
00:23:03,240 --> 00:23:04,400
How would I know?

586
00:23:07,520 --> 00:23:09,240
Just a reminder,

587
00:23:09,560 --> 00:23:11,240
Cao Yiyi

588
00:23:11,760 --> 00:23:14,000
has a crescent-shaped birthmark
on her back.

589
00:23:18,440 --> 00:23:20,000
You figure it out.

590
00:23:33,480 --> 00:23:33,880
Zijie,

591
00:23:34,040 --> 00:23:34,640
come here.

592
00:23:49,440 --> 00:23:50,760
Your mother repeatedly

593
00:23:51,040 --> 00:23:52,800
told me

594
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:53,840
to pass it on

595
00:23:53,960 --> 00:23:55,360
to your future wife.

596
00:23:59,520 --> 00:24:00,320
You should keep

597
00:24:00,960 --> 00:24:01,760
it safe now.

598
00:24:02,920 --> 00:24:03,640
That's not right.

599
00:24:03,720 --> 00:24:04,120
Father,

600
00:24:04,600 --> 00:24:05,640
Brother is the eldest son.

601
00:24:05,640 --> 00:24:07,760
This should be kept
for the eldest daughter-in-law.

602
00:24:08,040 --> 00:24:09,840
Just take it when I tell you so.

603
00:24:18,100 --> 00:24:19,140
Thank you, Father.

604
00:24:19,360 --> 00:24:20,840
You can get back to your business.

605
00:24:44,640 --> 00:24:45,880
That bracelet

606
00:24:46,400 --> 00:24:47,760
was left by your mother.

607
00:24:49,680 --> 00:24:52,600
It was promised to the future head
of the household's wife.

608
00:24:53,400 --> 00:24:54,200
Do you really think

609
00:24:54,920 --> 00:24:57,040
your father might want Guo Zijie

610
00:24:57,400 --> 00:24:58,960
to inherit the family business?

611
00:24:59,340 --> 00:25:00,120
Young Master Zilu,

612
00:25:00,600 --> 00:25:02,160
you're not worse than that fool.

613
00:25:02,180 --> 00:25:02,440
He...

614
00:25:02,440 --> 00:25:02,920
Shut up!

615
00:25:12,520 --> 00:25:13,200
He Chun,

616
00:25:13,680 --> 00:25:14,480
where are you going?

617
00:25:14,960 --> 00:25:16,820
This is the wooden board
we found earlier.

618
00:25:16,840 --> 00:25:18,000
I'll go and take care of it.

619
00:25:18,360 --> 00:25:19,080
Let me see.

620
00:25:27,320 --> 00:25:28,680
To be able to paint

621
00:25:28,680 --> 00:25:30,500
such a realistic house on a wooden board

622
00:25:30,920 --> 00:25:32,880
creates an optic illusion.

623
00:25:37,040 --> 00:25:38,600
Do you have

624
00:25:38,760 --> 00:25:39,920
any realist artists here?

625
00:25:40,600 --> 00:25:41,600
Realist artist?

626
00:25:44,600 --> 00:25:45,600
If you put it that way,

627
00:25:45,920 --> 00:25:46,920
there's a famous

628
00:25:46,920 --> 00:25:48,120
Western artist

629
00:25:48,120 --> 00:25:49,500
on the outskirts of the city.

630
00:25:49,920 --> 00:25:51,040
The paper,

631
00:25:51,200 --> 00:25:52,320
ink, and brushes he uses

632
00:25:52,760 --> 00:25:53,800
are special.

633
00:25:54,240 --> 00:25:55,400
Wealthy young ladies

634
00:25:55,400 --> 00:25:57,040
often go to him

635
00:25:57,280 --> 00:25:59,040
for portraits.

636
00:25:59,260 --> 00:26:00,840
He can really make them come to life.

637
00:26:01,240 --> 00:26:02,520
I know that artist.

638
00:26:03,440 --> 00:26:04,520
Do you suspect

639
00:26:05,040 --> 00:26:06,200
Zhao Qiang had an accomplice?

640
00:26:07,280 --> 00:26:08,080
I'm sure he couldn't

641
00:26:08,220 --> 00:26:10,100
come up
with such a tricky plan by himself.

642
00:26:10,760 --> 00:26:12,080
I'll go and meet that artist.

643
00:26:12,360 --> 00:26:12,960
Maybe

644
00:26:13,200 --> 00:26:14,160
I can find some answers.

645
00:26:14,680 --> 00:26:16,380
Then I leave this matter to both of you.

646
00:26:16,440 --> 00:26:17,180
No problem at all.

647
00:26:17,600 --> 00:26:18,180
Just go.

648
00:26:23,680 --> 00:26:24,360
Can I

649
00:26:24,640 --> 00:26:26,360
have a sip of water?

650
00:26:34,320 --> 00:26:35,200
It's wine.

651
00:26:35,200 --> 00:26:35,920
Move aside!

652
00:26:38,820 --> 00:26:39,900
Are you all right, mister?

653
00:26:39,900 --> 00:26:40,480
What's wrong?

654
00:26:40,480 --> 00:26:41,000
I'm so sorry.

655
00:26:41,200 --> 00:26:41,920
I'm sorry, mister.

656
00:26:42,480 --> 00:26:43,000
Are you hurt?

657
00:26:43,160 --> 00:26:43,640
I'm fine.

658
00:26:44,440 --> 00:26:45,280
Let me help you.

659
00:26:45,420 --> 00:26:46,240
Are you all right?

660
00:26:46,240 --> 00:26:47,200
Don't go too fast later.

661
00:26:47,200 --> 00:26:47,640
All right.

662
00:26:47,640 --> 00:26:48,560
Be more careful later!

663
00:26:48,640 --> 00:26:49,680
I will.

664
00:26:51,000 --> 00:26:51,600
This way.

665
00:27:01,360 --> 00:27:01,880
You're fine.

666
00:27:02,360 --> 00:27:03,700
Your vital points aren't injured.

667
00:27:04,600 --> 00:27:05,800
You're not the one injured.

668
00:27:05,800 --> 00:27:07,000
Of course, you don't feel pain.

669
00:27:07,160 --> 00:27:07,520
You...

670
00:27:08,080 --> 00:27:09,280
I'm in a lot of pain now.

671
00:27:11,480 --> 00:27:11,880
Get up.

672
00:27:12,320 --> 00:27:13,280
We need to keep going.

673
00:27:13,400 --> 00:27:14,520
I'm injured.

674
00:27:17,520 --> 00:27:18,360
Wait for me.

675
00:27:18,360 --> 00:27:19,160
Hurry up.

676
00:27:20,760 --> 00:27:21,560
How can I walk fast

677
00:27:21,560 --> 00:27:23,000
when I'm injured?

678
00:27:24,720 --> 00:27:25,160
Get on.

679
00:27:26,760 --> 00:27:27,920
I don't think that's proper.

680
00:27:27,980 --> 00:27:28,840
Stop wasting time.

681
00:27:28,900 --> 00:27:29,860
You're too slow.

682
00:27:30,080 --> 00:27:31,400
I'm a man.

683
00:27:31,400 --> 00:27:32,720
How can I let a woman carry me?

684
00:27:32,720 --> 00:27:33,680
I said, get on.

685
00:27:34,520 --> 00:27:35,640
The other hand.

686
00:27:39,940 --> 00:27:41,500
This isn't something we see every day.

687
00:27:42,140 --> 00:27:43,680
Why is she carrying him or her back?

688
00:27:43,680 --> 00:27:44,280
Are you tired?

689
00:27:48,240 --> 00:27:49,000
Actually,

690
00:27:49,280 --> 00:27:51,000
you can be quite gentle sometimes.

691
00:27:51,900 --> 00:27:53,520
Why is she carrying
that man on her back?

692
00:27:53,520 --> 00:27:53,960
Keep quiet.

693
00:27:54,640 --> 00:27:55,360
Look at that.

694
00:27:55,360 --> 00:27:56,200
That's something new.

695
00:27:56,240 --> 00:27:57,720
Why don't you put me down?

696
00:27:57,720 --> 00:27:58,460
I think I can walk.

697
00:27:58,460 --> 00:27:59,100
Stay still.

698
00:28:00,080 --> 00:28:01,000
Put me down.

699
00:28:01,000 --> 00:28:02,000
I think I can walk.

700
00:28:02,120 --> 00:28:03,080
You hurt your muscles.

701
00:28:03,080 --> 00:28:04,480
So it will be hard for you to walk.

702
00:28:05,240 --> 00:28:06,640
Come on. Put me down.

703
00:28:10,920 --> 00:28:12,640
I just said you were gentle
a moment ago.

704
00:28:15,100 --> 00:28:17,780
It's difficult to get along
with women and petty people.

705
00:28:21,080 --> 00:28:21,640
Get up.

706
00:28:22,080 --> 00:28:23,940
Up ahead is the stall
of a Western artist.

707
00:28:24,440 --> 00:28:24,920
Hurry.

708
00:28:31,760 --> 00:28:32,240
Jeez.

709
00:28:32,600 --> 00:28:33,640
Wait for me!

710
00:28:39,160 --> 00:28:40,800
I almost couldn't catch up with you.

711
00:28:44,480 --> 00:28:45,360
Excuse me,

712
00:28:45,360 --> 00:28:46,480
would you like a painting?

713
00:28:47,080 --> 00:28:47,600
Mister,

714
00:28:48,040 --> 00:28:49,200
did you draw these?

715
00:28:49,360 --> 00:28:49,720
No.

716
00:28:50,240 --> 00:28:51,640
A Western artist did.

717
00:28:51,800 --> 00:28:52,560
He's ill.

718
00:28:53,200 --> 00:28:53,840
So

719
00:28:53,940 --> 00:28:55,660
I'm helping him to sell his paintings.

720
00:28:56,080 --> 00:28:57,080
How about buying one?

721
00:28:59,400 --> 00:29:00,000
Mister,

722
00:29:00,280 --> 00:29:02,120
do you know when this

723
00:29:02,120 --> 00:29:03,300
Western artist will return?

724
00:29:03,400 --> 00:29:04,440
He told me

725
00:29:04,560 --> 00:29:06,600
to watch his stall for a couple of days.

726
00:29:07,000 --> 00:29:08,120
I think he'll come back

727
00:29:08,120 --> 00:29:09,440
the day after tomorrow.

728
00:29:15,261 --> 00:29:17,220
(He's Apothecary)

729
00:29:20,680 --> 00:29:21,080
Miss.

730
00:29:21,440 --> 00:29:22,080
What's this?

731
00:29:23,560 --> 00:29:24,520
This is...

732
00:29:25,360 --> 00:29:26,080
Healing powder

733
00:29:26,120 --> 00:29:27,900
to improve blood flow
and clear blood clots.

734
00:29:30,360 --> 00:29:31,080
Thank you.

735
00:29:34,560 --> 00:29:34,840
Then

736
00:29:35,040 --> 00:29:36,160
what do you have there?

737
00:29:36,280 --> 00:29:36,840
Are you ill?

738
00:29:37,420 --> 00:29:38,360
I suffer from insomnia.

739
00:29:38,600 --> 00:29:39,240
I can't sleep.

740
00:29:39,840 --> 00:29:41,840
I didn't know you would suffer
from insomnia.

741
00:29:46,960 --> 00:29:47,400
Miss,

742
00:29:48,320 --> 00:29:49,720
Guo Residence is that way.

743
00:29:49,880 --> 00:29:50,600
We're too far.

744
00:29:50,680 --> 00:29:51,520
How do we go back?

745
00:29:52,640 --> 00:29:53,560
Then where do we go?

746
00:30:13,040 --> 00:30:13,600
Miss He,

747
00:30:14,080 --> 00:30:15,000
where are we?

748
00:30:22,720 --> 00:30:23,960
Is this your house?

749
00:30:24,760 --> 00:30:26,240
It's different from what I imagined.

750
00:30:28,760 --> 00:30:29,320
Is

751
00:30:29,400 --> 00:30:30,280
your grandpa not home?

752
00:30:31,560 --> 00:30:32,800
He is in the countryside.

753
00:30:33,360 --> 00:30:34,160
Let's make do

754
00:30:34,320 --> 00:30:35,600
with staying here for the night.

755
00:30:39,880 --> 00:30:40,320
But

756
00:30:40,600 --> 00:30:41,640
there's only one bed.

757
00:30:42,000 --> 00:30:43,080
How can we sleep?

758
00:30:43,880 --> 00:30:45,360
You'll sleep in the bed.

759
00:30:48,120 --> 00:30:49,200
How is that proper?

760
00:30:49,200 --> 00:30:50,320
You should sleep in the bed.

761
00:30:50,380 --> 00:30:51,440
I can make do.

762
00:30:52,280 --> 00:30:54,160
Martial artists like us
don't care about this.

763
00:30:58,840 --> 00:30:59,680
All right, then.

764
00:31:08,840 --> 00:31:09,800
I'll see you tomorrow.

765
00:31:18,040 --> 00:31:18,800
What's the matter?

766
00:31:19,720 --> 00:31:20,320
What is it?

767
00:31:21,840 --> 00:31:23,240
Who told you to blow out the candle?

768
00:31:23,260 --> 00:31:23,960
I'm going to bed.

769
00:31:23,960 --> 00:31:25,320
How can I not blow out the candle?

770
00:31:25,400 --> 00:31:26,180
Don't blow it out!

771
00:31:26,240 --> 00:31:26,900
Light it!

772
00:31:27,780 --> 00:31:29,240
But I don't have a fire starter.

773
00:31:29,240 --> 00:31:30,640
There's one in the cabinet.

774
00:31:32,220 --> 00:31:33,280
What is this situation...

775
00:31:34,940 --> 00:31:36,200
I can't get the fire starter

776
00:31:36,200 --> 00:31:37,280
if you don't let me go.

777
00:31:38,040 --> 00:31:38,720
Don't be scared.

778
00:31:39,160 --> 00:31:39,920
Here, sit here.

779
00:31:40,240 --> 00:31:41,520
I'll go and get the fire starter.

780
00:31:41,520 --> 00:31:42,280
I'll be right back.

781
00:31:50,440 --> 00:31:51,360
Is it at the bottom?

782
00:31:51,720 --> 00:31:52,160
Yes.

783
00:31:54,400 --> 00:31:55,560
Hurry up!

784
00:31:56,400 --> 00:31:57,000
I found it.

785
00:32:13,440 --> 00:32:14,800
Hurry up.

786
00:32:14,800 --> 00:32:16,360
This fire starter won't light.

787
00:32:16,960 --> 00:32:18,000
Why are you so stupid?

788
00:32:18,080 --> 00:32:19,740
You can't even start a fire with it.

789
00:32:21,480 --> 00:32:22,320
Say that again.

790
00:32:24,360 --> 00:32:25,600
I'm doing you a favor here.

791
00:32:28,360 --> 00:32:29,120
I didn't expect

792
00:32:29,640 --> 00:32:31,160
a heroine to be afraid of the dark.

793
00:32:31,400 --> 00:32:32,520
That's pretty adorable.

794
00:32:35,340 --> 00:32:36,760
If you dare tell anyone about this,

795
00:32:37,440 --> 00:32:38,280
I will kill you.

796
00:32:40,280 --> 00:32:41,360
Fine. I won't tell a soul.

797
00:32:41,940 --> 00:32:42,560
This thing...

798
00:32:42,640 --> 00:32:44,480
It's not lighting up
after blowing on it.

799
00:32:45,520 --> 00:32:46,480
What now?

800
00:32:48,120 --> 00:32:48,640
Then...

801
00:32:50,240 --> 00:32:51,000
Then

802
00:32:51,200 --> 00:32:52,240
I'll just keep you company.

803
00:32:53,120 --> 00:32:54,480
You won't be scared that way.

804
00:33:02,060 --> 00:33:03,540
(Guo Residence)

805
00:33:04,600 --> 00:33:05,360
What do you want?

806
00:33:05,360 --> 00:33:06,400
Hurry up.

807
00:33:10,320 --> 00:33:11,000
There you go.

808
00:33:12,040 --> 00:33:13,680
You want me to write again?

809
00:33:14,060 --> 00:33:15,020
I don't want to write.

810
00:33:15,020 --> 00:33:16,760
I can't write
when there's no inspiration.

811
00:33:16,780 --> 00:33:17,820
You have no choice.

812
00:33:17,920 --> 00:33:18,600
Write it now.

813
00:33:26,240 --> 00:33:26,960
I get it.

814
00:33:27,440 --> 00:33:28,320
Are you trying

815
00:33:28,600 --> 00:33:29,480
to help me sort out

816
00:33:29,520 --> 00:33:30,360
the thoughts

817
00:33:30,600 --> 00:33:32,400
for this brilliant work of creation?

818
00:33:34,760 --> 00:33:35,520
I knew

819
00:33:36,000 --> 00:33:36,640
you cared

820
00:33:36,720 --> 00:33:37,720
about me.

821
00:33:37,920 --> 00:33:39,160
Who says I care about you.

822
00:33:41,360 --> 00:33:42,160
I've written

823
00:33:42,440 --> 00:33:43,400
this one down.

824
00:33:43,440 --> 00:33:45,080
You can copy word by word
into your book.

825
00:33:45,080 --> 00:33:46,140
Then your book is complete.

826
00:33:49,280 --> 00:33:51,200
(The principle of this case:
Optical Illusion.)

827
00:33:55,080 --> 00:33:56,000
If you ask me,

828
00:33:56,020 --> 00:33:56,680
you really need

829
00:33:56,680 --> 00:33:57,860
to practice your writing.

830
00:33:58,540 --> 00:34:00,320
Do you want to learn
how to write?

831
00:34:00,520 --> 00:34:01,120
If you beg me,

832
00:34:01,360 --> 00:34:02,160
I can teach you.

833
00:34:02,840 --> 00:34:04,080
These are simplified characters,

834
00:34:04,080 --> 00:34:05,200
not incorrect characters.

835
00:34:05,920 --> 00:34:06,800
Simplified?

836
00:34:07,340 --> 00:34:08,300
See for yourself.

837
00:34:08,380 --> 00:34:09,600
It's either missing a side part

838
00:34:09,600 --> 00:34:10,560
or a radical.

839
00:34:10,920 --> 00:34:11,720
Simplified, huh?

840
00:34:11,780 --> 00:34:12,920
I've never heard of that...

841
00:34:12,920 --> 00:34:14,480
What would an illiterate like you know?

842
00:34:14,480 --> 00:34:15,220
Just write it now.

843
00:34:15,240 --> 00:34:15,720
No.

844
00:34:15,920 --> 00:34:16,160
You...

845
00:34:16,480 --> 00:34:16,960
I can't.

846
00:34:17,820 --> 00:34:18,600
I can teach you.

847
00:34:18,680 --> 00:34:19,680
Do you know how to write?

848
00:34:19,680 --> 00:34:20,820
Write your name for me.

849
00:34:22,760 --> 00:34:23,880
Mr. Sun, you're back.

850
00:34:24,000 --> 00:34:24,320
Yes.

851
00:34:24,440 --> 00:34:25,480
Tell us what you found.

852
00:34:25,480 --> 00:34:26,040
Tell us.

853
00:34:26,040 --> 00:34:26,360
I...

854
00:34:27,860 --> 00:34:29,080
You can ask from here.

855
00:34:29,160 --> 00:34:30,420
Why are you standing so close?

856
00:34:31,860 --> 00:34:32,680
Please be seated.

857
00:34:39,760 --> 00:34:40,320
Mr. Sun,

858
00:34:40,840 --> 00:34:42,200
have you found that Western artist?

859
00:34:43,200 --> 00:34:44,000
We found his stall.

860
00:34:44,000 --> 00:34:44,840
But he wasn't there.

861
00:34:44,960 --> 00:34:46,320
They said he'll come back tomorrow.

862
00:34:47,000 --> 00:34:47,960
Tomorrow, huh?

863
00:34:48,480 --> 00:34:48,840
Fine.

864
00:34:48,840 --> 00:34:50,220
We'll check it out again tomorrow.

865
00:34:51,420 --> 00:34:52,720
He is attending a banquet?

866
00:34:53,040 --> 00:34:53,520
Yes.

867
00:34:54,120 --> 00:34:54,880
He went

868
00:34:54,880 --> 00:34:56,800
to attend Mr. Lyu's banquet.

869
00:34:58,080 --> 00:35:00,800
Mr. Lyu had him painted
his portrait before.

870
00:35:01,040 --> 00:35:03,520
He highly respects his painting skills.

871
00:35:03,960 --> 00:35:05,880
You mean Lyu Bufan
from outside the city?

872
00:35:06,200 --> 00:35:07,120
Yes,

873
00:35:07,200 --> 00:35:08,600
that Mr. Lyu.

874
00:35:08,840 --> 00:35:09,600
Do you know him?

875
00:35:10,840 --> 00:35:12,640
I received his wedding invitation
yesterday.

876
00:35:13,240 --> 00:35:13,960
But

877
00:35:14,200 --> 00:35:15,160
we aren't close.

878
00:35:15,520 --> 00:35:17,020
Since you've received the invitation,

879
00:35:17,040 --> 00:35:18,600
people can get close over drinks.

880
00:35:19,240 --> 00:35:20,360
We're not on the same page.

881
00:35:20,480 --> 00:35:21,880
Forget about a wedding reception,

882
00:35:21,920 --> 00:35:23,000
even drinking nuptial wine

883
00:35:23,060 --> 00:35:24,360
can't change our direction.

884
00:35:28,480 --> 00:35:29,640
If you help me this time,

885
00:35:30,120 --> 00:35:31,000
I'll help you

886
00:35:31,180 --> 00:35:32,000
with future cases.

887
00:35:35,460 --> 00:35:36,200
All right, then.

888
00:35:39,820 --> 00:35:40,760
(Lyu Residence)
Welcome.

889
00:35:40,760 --> 00:35:41,880
This way, please.

890
00:35:41,880 --> 00:35:43,560
Congratulations.

891
00:35:44,840 --> 00:35:45,480
You're late.

892
00:35:47,200 --> 00:35:48,160
Congratulations.

893
00:35:48,760 --> 00:35:49,840
Feng, Li.

894
00:35:50,240 --> 00:35:51,000
It's truly an honor

895
00:35:51,120 --> 00:35:52,520
to have you here.

896
00:35:56,040 --> 00:35:56,980
Please head inside.

897
00:35:57,360 --> 00:35:57,920
Welcome, Wang.

898
00:36:01,060 --> 00:36:02,200
So this is Lyu Residence.

899
00:36:03,320 --> 00:36:04,120
Please come inside.

900
00:36:05,160 --> 00:36:06,440
I'll catch up with you later.

901
00:36:07,000 --> 00:36:07,800
Together, all right?

902
00:36:09,280 --> 00:36:09,880
Hello, Lyu.

903
00:36:10,080 --> 00:36:11,300
Oh, my! It's Magistrate Guo.

904
00:36:12,480 --> 00:36:13,120
Congratulations.

905
00:36:13,120 --> 00:36:14,090
Mr. Lyu, congratulations.

906
00:36:14,090 --> 00:36:14,640
Thank you!

907
00:36:15,220 --> 00:36:15,920
Hold these.

908
00:36:16,640 --> 00:36:17,220
Gentlemen,

909
00:36:17,360 --> 00:36:18,680
let me make the introduction.

910
00:36:19,040 --> 00:36:19,680
This person

911
00:36:19,880 --> 00:36:21,600
is the county magistrate of Yan City,

912
00:36:21,800 --> 00:36:23,120
Magistrate Guo Zijie.

913
00:36:24,000 --> 00:36:25,260
Magistrate Guo, how do you do.

914
00:36:26,600 --> 00:36:27,320
Magistrate Guo,

915
00:36:27,840 --> 00:36:29,000
this is Zhou Shui

916
00:36:29,160 --> 00:36:29,920
and Zheng Si.

917
00:36:30,920 --> 00:36:31,240
This one

918
00:36:31,320 --> 00:36:32,320
is Mr. Luo Ji.

919
00:36:32,600 --> 00:36:33,960
They're all my good friends.

920
00:36:36,540 --> 00:36:37,800
This man is no ordinary person.

921
00:36:38,000 --> 00:36:39,840
He's the palace favorite, Eunuch Wang.

922
00:36:39,900 --> 00:36:40,820
Let's meet each other.

923
00:36:40,840 --> 00:36:41,820
Greetings, Eunuch Wang.

924
00:36:45,360 --> 00:36:47,580
Hua, show Magistrate Guo
and the others the way inside.

925
00:36:47,600 --> 00:36:48,500
Magistrate Guo, please.

926
00:36:48,520 --> 00:36:49,160
Serve him well.

927
00:36:49,160 --> 00:36:49,440
Yes.

928
00:36:50,020 --> 00:36:51,160
Magistrate Guo, this way.

929
00:36:51,160 --> 00:36:51,960
Please come inside.

930
00:36:52,960 --> 00:36:54,400
Magistrate Guo is finally here.

931
00:36:56,080 --> 00:36:56,640
Hurry.

932
00:36:57,000 --> 00:36:57,600
Magistrate Guo,

933
00:36:57,880 --> 00:36:58,580
forgive me.

934
00:36:58,580 --> 00:36:59,960
We don't have many guest rooms left

935
00:37:00,020 --> 00:37:01,480
and there are so many of you.

936
00:37:04,280 --> 00:37:05,920
Miss He Chun and I can share a room.

937
00:37:07,120 --> 00:37:07,540
But...

938
00:37:07,590 --> 00:37:08,400
That would work too.

939
00:37:08,400 --> 00:37:10,040
Aren't you used to living alone?

940
00:37:10,360 --> 00:37:11,200
Why are you...

941
00:37:12,680 --> 00:37:13,440
I'm afraid

942
00:37:13,780 --> 00:37:15,280
someone might have bad intentions.

943
00:37:15,280 --> 00:37:16,560
I feel safer with you around.

944
00:37:17,880 --> 00:37:18,680
By the way,

945
00:37:19,280 --> 00:37:21,120
we've just imported
Dragon Spring Water here.

946
00:37:21,200 --> 00:37:22,090
I'll have it delivered

947
00:37:22,090 --> 00:37:22,960
to your room shortly.

948
00:37:22,980 --> 00:37:23,280
Sure.

949
00:37:23,280 --> 00:37:24,400
We can enjoy the hot spring?

950
00:37:24,420 --> 00:37:24,860
Yes.

951
00:37:24,860 --> 00:37:25,400
This way.

952
00:37:25,460 --> 00:37:26,140
Let's go.

953
00:38:16,320 --> 00:38:22,200
♪Like the setting sun,
which repeatedly sets in the west♪

954
00:38:23,460 --> 00:38:28,900
♪My heart goes over mountains
to rest with you♪

955
00:38:30,060 --> 00:38:33,500
♪As the winds and clouds shift,
our encounter♪

956
00:38:33,500 --> 00:38:37,260
♪Seems like the perfect foreshadowing♪

957
00:38:37,660 --> 00:38:42,700
♪But it was a misplaced expectation♪

958
00:38:44,220 --> 00:38:47,300
♪I think I'm exceptionally affectionate♪

959
00:38:47,500 --> 00:38:50,420
♪Devotion can warm the coldest ice♪

960
00:38:50,780 --> 00:38:53,980
♪And you're a shooting star
that flashes by♪

961
00:38:54,420 --> 00:38:56,700
♪Out of reach♪

962
00:38:57,780 --> 00:39:00,980
♪I prayed for a miracle countless times♪

963
00:39:01,260 --> 00:39:05,380
♪If I meet you, I only wish
we could be together forever♪

964
00:39:05,660 --> 00:39:11,780
♪But only the distant phantom remains♪

965
00:39:11,900 --> 00:39:14,940
♪Love rises like the wind
but remains unsettled when it stops♪

966
00:39:15,220 --> 00:39:18,220
♪Chasing you through four seasons,
wandering for a lifetime♪

967
00:39:18,500 --> 00:39:20,180
♪Fish in the water♪

968
00:39:20,180 --> 00:39:25,420
♪Is greedy for the reflection
of clouds in the heart of the lake♪

969
00:39:25,620 --> 00:39:28,540
♪From dusk to dawn,
from heavy snow to early clear sky♪

970
00:39:28,740 --> 00:39:33,060
♪Searching for your footprints
from south to west♪

971
00:39:33,420 --> 00:39:39,060
♪The wind stops,
but the dream isn't over♪
